returns.contentHash: The content hash of the matching version.

params.contentHash: The hash of the content being versioned.
params.metadata: Arbitrary metadata associated with this version.
params.validFrom: The start of the valid time range.
params.validTo: The end of the valid time range.

returns.versionId: The unique identifier for this version.

returns.newVersionId: The identifier of the new version.

asOf(uint256,uint256).notice: Finds a version that was active at the given system time and valid time.

between(uint256,uint256,string).notice: Returns versions within a time range for a given dimension.

getVersion(bytes32).notice: Retrieves a version entry by ID.

supersede(bytes32,bytes32).notice: Supersedes a version with new content, closing the old version's system time.

versionCount().notice: Returns the total number of versions recorded.
